  <compounddef id="classdynamic_21" kind="predicate" language="Prolog" prot="public">
    <compoundname>dynamic/1</compoundname>
    <briefdescription>
<para><bold>dynamic</bold>( + <emphasis>P</emphasis> ) </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Declares predicate <emphasis>P</emphasis> or list of predicates [ <emphasis>P1</emphasis>,..., <emphasis>Pn</emphasis>] as a dynamic predicate <emphasis>P</emphasis> must be written as a predicate indicator, that is in form <emphasis>Name/Arity</emphasis> or <emphasis>Module:Name/Arity</emphasis></para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal">:-<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">dynamic</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>@</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal">god/1<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">.</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>a more convenient form can be used:</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keyword">:-</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">dynamic</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>@</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal">son/3<sp/>,<sp/>@</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal">father/2<sp/>,<sp/>@</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal">mother/2<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">.</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>or, equivalently,</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keyword">:-</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">dynamic</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>[</highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal">son/3,<sp/>@ref<sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal">father/2<sp/>,<sp/>@ref<sp/></highlight><highlight class="stringliteral"></highlight><highlight class="normal">mother/2<sp/>]</highlight><highlight class="keyword">.</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Note:</para>
<para>a predicate is assumed to be dynamic when asserted before being defined </para>
    </detaileddescription>
